The U.S. government has appointed Penny Pritzker as the new U.S. Special Representative for Ukraine's Economic Recovery. Pritzker, a former Secretary of Commerce, will work with the Ukrainian government, allies, international financial institutions, and the private sector to rebuild the Ukrainian economy. Her responsibilities include mobilizing investment, shaping donor priorities, and reopening export markets and businesses affected by Russia's attacks. Pritzker will also coordinate with Ukraine's international partners to ensure a unified approach and encourage continued support for Ukraine's economic recovery. She will assist the Ukrainian government in implementing necessary reforms to strengthen the economy and ensure that Ukraine rebuilds even stronger. The United States remains committed to supporting Ukraine's freedom and standing with its people.